There is quite a bit of history of the loadbalancer. There is one specific issue which prevents OpenWhisk to be auto-loadbalanced by Kafka's partitioning: locality.

Our loadbalancer has a very strong locality constraint. We need to make use of warm containers as much as possible to keep performance numbers anywhere acceptable. Balancing via consumer groups won't give us that locality necessarily. Do you know how if it's possible to implement that constraint on consumer groups?

@tysonnorris proposed a change to our topic design which is being implemented on the dev list. You might want to look that up for some more context.
